The defendant Nichole Marie Ulrichsen was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Letter to defendant in response to question about commencement of sentence.

Defendant Nichole Marie Ulrichsen in court with attorney Alexis Liggins.  Defendant Nichole Marie Ulrichsen in custody.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Case calendared for sentencing hearing.  Case passed.

TAPE# 10:09:17
CASE RECALLED.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Court sentenced defendant to serve 90 DAYS in the House of Correction; Huber privileges for treatment. 

Court ordered the defendant to pay restitution in the amount of $50.00 to Reflection Pawn Shop, 1306 W Forest Home Avenue, Milwaukee, WI  53204 by August 5, 2016 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.  Court ordered defendant to pay ALL COSTS and SURCHARGES by August 5, 2016 or, as a penalty if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.

Defendant Nichole Marie Ulrichsen in court with attorney Alexis Liggins.  Defendant Nichole Marie Ulrichsen in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Additional statements by victim, Ricky C.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 24.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 5, 2015 at 08:30 am.
ORDER TO PRODUCE, THURSDAY JULY 09, 2015 AT 1:30 P.M. IN BR 24, CH RM 622. kl

Attorney Alexis Liggins in court, defendant Nichole Marie Ulrichsen not in court, in custody.  Daniel J. Gabler appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  The defendant is in custody in Waukesha County on a pending felony matter.  Deputy Cleveland verified the defendant's custody status.  Court ordered the previously issued warrant canceled but issued a bench warrant and stayed it until the next court date.  Court ordered case adjourned for projected guilty plea in Branch 24.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for July 9, 2015 at 01:30 pm.
